  <RulesElement name="Goblin-Blackblade" type="Background" internal-id="ID_MSR_BACKGROUND_200" source="ObMeiste" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:34:59 PM">
    <specific name="type"> Striker </specific>
    <specific name="Common Knowledge"> You carry with you your namesake weapon, sootblackened so that it's gleam might be as hidden as yourself, moments before you spring on an unsuspecting foe to stain it crimson.
Of all goblins you most embody the soft-footed nature of your kind, going unseen and unheard when it is called for. For this reason you often take up the mantle of scout, or the front-line warrior as part of an ambush. In each role your talent is honed to see and take advantage of each slip up and opening presented by the opposition. </specific>
    <specific name="Benefit"> Features
-Stealthy: You gain the stealth skill as a class skill. If your selected class already has it listed you gain +2 bonus to that skill.
-Combat Advantage: Deals 1d6 extra damage against any target it has combat advantage against.
-Sneaky: When shifting you can move into a space occupied by an ally. The ally shifts into your previous space as a free action. </specific>
    <specific name="Short Description"/>
    <specific name="Campaign"> General </specific>
    <specific name="Associated Skills"/>
    <specific name="Associated Languages"/>
    <rules>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BLACKBLADE_1" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BLACKBLADE_2" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BLACKBLADE_3" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_INTERNAL_BACKGROUND_ASSOCIATION_STEALTH" type="Background Association"/>
    </rules>
  </RulesElement>
