  <RulesElement name="Goblin-Bloodthorn" type="Background" internal-id="ID_MSR_BACKGROUND_201" source="ObMeiste" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:34:59 PM">
    <specific name="type"> Striker </specific>
    <specific name="Common Knowledge"> Small and weak, goblins aren't much in a straight up fight and thus cleverly rarely get involved in them. Bloodthorns like the blackblades adhere to this principle, but instead of opting for going unseen they prefer to go untouched. Moving quickly about they evade their foes as they harry them with missile fire from position of great advantage.
Even if their foes can manage to close, they deftly dive back from any blow before moving aside while delivering one more thorn into their foes side. </specific>
    <specific name="Benefit"> Features
-Nimble: You gain the acrobatics skill as a class skill. If your selected class already has it listed you gain +2 bonus to that skill.
-Great position: If, on your turn, you ends your move at least 4 squares away from your starting position, you deal 1d6 extra damage on your ranged attack until the start of your next turn.
-Mobile Ranged Attack: You gain the mobile ranged attack at-will </specific>
    <specific name="Short Description"/>
    <specific name="Campaign"> General </specific>
    <specific name="Associated Skills"/>
    <specific name="Associated Languages"/>
    <rules>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BLOODTHORN_1" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BLOODTHORN_2" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BLOODTHORN_3" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_INTERNAL_BACKGROUND_ASSOCIATION_ACROBATICS" type="Background Association"/>
    </rules>
  </RulesElement>
