  <RulesElement name="Goblin-Beast Marshall" type="Background" internal-id="ID_MSR_BACKGROUND_202" source="ObMeiste" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:34:59 PM">
    <specific name="type"> Leader </specific>
    <specific name="Common Knowledge"> Some measure of the legendary skill of goblin beastmasters from the ancient empire is carried on in you. For that reason you hold a great position in the tribe as the one to turn for council on dealing with the many savage beasts that come through the territory. A number of these creatures are often brought in to be tamed by you, to be used in the service of the clan as guardians. One of them even serves you loyally now, fighting by your side when need be and aiding you in your to show your mastery over other beasts. </specific>
    <specific name="Benefit"> Features
-Handler: You gain the nature skill as a class skill. If your selected class already has it listed you gain +2 bonus to that skill
-Beast Companion: You gain an animal companion as per the ranger class's beast mastery fighting style, although it has 1 healing surge. (Note if you've picked the actual feature as part of your later stage development you do no get a second animal companion upon finishing your development. Instead your animal companion gains +1 to all defenses and 2 extra healing surges.)
-Command the predator: You gain the command the predator at-will </specific>
    <specific name="Short Description"/>
    <specific name="Campaign"> General </specific>
    <specific name="Associated Skills"/>
    <specific name="Associated Languages"/>
    <rules>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BEASTM_1" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BEASTM_2" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_BEASTM_3" type="Class Feature"/>
      <grant name="ID_INTERNAL_BACKGROUND_ASSOCIATION_NATURE" type="Background Association"/>
    </rules>
  </RulesElement>
