  <RulesElement name="Goblin - Acolyte of Maglubiyet" type="Background" internal-id="ID_MSR_BACKGROUND_204" source="ObMeiste" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:34:59 PM">
    <specific name="type"> Leader </specific>
    <specific name="Common Knowledge"> Although but an Exarch of Bane, Maglubiyet is held in the same reverence as the black hand himself among his goblin servants. So while those goblins who focus more outwards towards conquest call to Bane, those more inclined to helping preparing their community, for their time to march to war, look more towards Maglubiyet.
While not a kind god, The Mighty One has foresight as a great general and provides through his servants as needed to goblin communities to help make them strong. His servants show the same skill of leadership and while some may be harsher than others, they do not accept defeat and do what they can to strengthen their tribes. </specific>
    <specific name="Benefit"> Features
-Priest: You gain the religion skill as a class skill. If your selected class already has it listed you gain a +2 bonus to that skill
-Ritualist: You gain the ritual caster feat. If your developing class gains it for free you may switch it later for alchemist, expert ritualist, or 150 gp worth of rituals.
-Maglubiyets warding hand: You gain Maglubiyets warding hand encounter power. </specific>
    <specific name="Short Description"/>
    <specific name="Campaign"> General </specific>
    <specific name="Associated Skills"/>
    <specific name="Associated Languages"/>
    <rules>
      <grant name="ID_MSR_GOBLIN_ACOLYTE_1" type="Class Feature"/>
